==English==

===Alternative spellings===
'''kotow'''

===Etymology===
Cantonese Chinese [[叩頭]] / [[叩头]] (kau3 tau4), ''kau3'' knock + ''tau4'' head

===Intransitive Verb===
'''to kowtow''' ('''kowtowed''', '''kowtowing''')

# To [[kneel]] and [[bow]] low enough to touch one's [[forehead]] to the ground.
# To [[bow]] very deeply.
# To act in a very [[submissive]] manner.

===Noun===
'''kowtow'''  (''plural:'' '''[[kowtows]]''')
# The act of kowtowing.

